vera++
------------------------------------------
Vera++ is a programmable tool for verification, analysis and transformation of
C++ source code. Vera++ is mainly an engine that parses C++ source files and
presents the result of this parsing to scripts in the form of various
collections - the scripts are actually performing the requested tasks.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libboost_filesystem1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_program_options1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_python3_1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_regex1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_system1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_wave1.66-1.66.0-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  liblua5.3-5.3.6-4
  libluabind0-0.9.1+git20150408-1bl2
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  python39-3.9.16-1
  tcl-8.6.12-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cmake-4.1.3-1
  cygport-0.37.4-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libboost-devel-1.66.0-1
  liblua-devel-5.3.6-4
  libluabind-devel-0.9.1+git20150408-1bl2
  lua-5.3.6-4
  ninja-1.13.2-1
  tcl-devel-8.6.12-1

Canonical website:
  https://bitbucket.org/verateam/vera/wiki/Home

Canonical download:
  https://bitbucket.org/verateam/vera/get/v1.3.0.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack vera++-1.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./vera++-1.3.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/vera++-1.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/vera++-1.3.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

